And in Colombia I went out and I went to Chile and Argentina and foolish people,

00:33:26.265 --> 00:33:31.152
they said, if Christ was not born a poor man then he would have been more effective.

00:33:31.177 --> 00:33:38.112
I said, how to talk of this man?

00:33:38.137 --> 00:33:43.272
You see, if Christ was a king, king is a temperament.

00:33:43.297 --> 00:33:49.892
Those who are hanker of things, how can they be kings?

00:33:49.917 --> 00:33:52.332
The king is a satisfied soul.

00:33:52.357 --> 00:33:58.172
Supposing you make me sleep here, I'll sleep here. If you make me sleep there, I'll sleep there.

00:33:58.197 --> 00:34:01.152
Such a person doesn't need anything.

00:34:01.177 --> 00:34:10.056
How much do you need really?

00:34:10.140 --> 00:34:13.578
(unclear)

00:34:13.603 --> 00:34:19.092
You see, whatever you want to do out of Me, I am here. And I will fulfill you.

00:34:19.117 --> 00:34:24.473
And I have told Mr. Varadarajan that I would love to be in the villages here

00:34:24.498 --> 00:34:27.832
and I am for them. But here I have come.

00:34:27.857 --> 00:34:31.972
It's a good thing in a way. I must praise your minister very much.

00:34:31.997 --> 00:34:34.952
I met him for the first time. But I liked him for one thing.

00:34:34.977 --> 00:34:38.492
He is such a rare person.

00:34:38.517 --> 00:34:45.232
I mean, to think, he said that this is the heritage of our Mother Earth.

00:34:45.257 --> 00:34:47.812
Dharohaya. You may mean like this, Dharohaya.

00:34:47.837 --> 00:34:53.992
This is the heritage of the Mother Earth. We should project this instead of casinos.

00:34:54.017 --> 00:34:58.532
You see, they have casinos, they have ballroom dancing, much better than you have.

00:34:58.557 --> 00:35:00.792
Actually, nobody comes to India with that idea.

00:35:00.817 --> 00:35:04.452
They come here for peace, for bliss, about which they know all.

00:35:04.477 --> 00:35:07.772
While they come here, you give them cheap cheer and this and that.

00:35:07.797 --> 00:35:12.492
They do not want it. You ask all of them.

00:35:12.517 --> 00:35:16.272
They come for peace and for relaxation.

00:35:16.297 --> 00:35:23.252
And he said that, that we should project this instead of projecting their sort of nuances.

00:35:23.277 --> 00:35:26.794
That's why perhaps I am in England, because English can teach us, Sahaja

00:35:26.819 --> 00:35:33.982
but we won't learn directly from it.

00:35:34.007 --> 00:35:43.412
Is it so, that we have to learn from English?

00:35:43.437 --> 00:35:47.172
Huh? (unclear)

00:35:47.197 --> 00:35:51.292
If you want to have experience or anything, you can stay on. I would like to see.

00:35:51.317 --> 00:35:53.452
And moreover, one more point I would like to see,

00:35:53.477 --> 00:35:59.552
because Khajurji has read that there is a village where people are suffering from illness.

00:35:59.577 --> 00:36:01.577
There's all these things which you...

00:36:01.577 --> 00:36:03.712
Yes, you have to neutralize it.

00:36:03.737 --> 00:36:06.537
How do you leave those things? You neutralize it, isn't it?

00:36:06.537 --> 00:36:07.197
Yes, you neutralize.

00:36:07.197 --> 00:36:10.997
Because otherwise people are not going to give up one thing to accept another until you become...

00:36:10.997 --> 00:36:12.497
But this is what our Sahaja Yoga...

00:36:12.497 --> 00:36:13.652
...so tangible.

00:36:13.677 --> 00:36:14.632
Yes, I know.

00:36:14.657 --> 00:36:17.532
This means that you... Yes, but you must become a political thought.

00:36:17.557 --> 00:36:21.692
No, no, no, not at all. Then you go from one extreme to another extreme.

00:36:21.717 --> 00:36:26.772
You see, you don't become politically, why? But you be free within yourself.

00:36:26.797 --> 00:36:29.292
Then you do not jump from one to another.

00:36:29.317 --> 00:36:31.092
But then how can you win? How can you win?

00:36:31.117 --> 00:36:33.397
I mean, people are not going to leave those...

00:36:33.397 --> 00:36:37.972
They will, they will. We can neutralize. We have power to neutralize them.

00:36:37.997 --> 00:36:39.877
They will. You see, the winning is which way?

00:36:39.877 --> 00:36:42.752
You need you need millions of these people.

00:36:42.777 --> 00:36:47.172
We have, we have to have. We will get them. We will get them.

00:36:47.197 --> 00:36:50.452
There are so many ways we can work it out. For example, cancer.

00:36:50.477 --> 00:36:54.257
You cannot cure cancer except through this. You must get your Self-realization.

00:36:54.257 --> 00:36:58.192
So all the cancer people, let them come down.

00:36:58.217 --> 00:37:00.672
We have a doctor here. He's practicing in London.

00:37:00.697 --> 00:37:05.432
And now I've cured a doctor's wife of cancer.

00:37:05.457 --> 00:37:10.012
So they will have to accept this. They will come. They will come.

00:37:10.037 --> 00:37:12.412
They will have to accept. There are so many other ways.

00:37:12.437 --> 00:37:15.032
You can make them understand.

00:37:15.057 --> 00:37:19.357
Well, do you have a cast in London because there were a lot of...

00:37:19.357 --> 00:37:24.272
We had one lady working very hard in Tehran with another rat.

00:37:24.297 --> 00:37:25.452
Where is that?

00:37:25.477 --> 00:37:28.952
London Sahaja Yoga Center. You can give them.

00:37:28.977 --> 00:37:33.651
Like everybody else, they're all refugees now. And they're all in a bad state.

00:37:33.676 --> 00:37:36.452
So if, like, we ask to get in touch with them.

00:37:36.477 --> 00:37:39.412
Just a minute. Can you give it one of the things?

00:37:39.437 --> 00:37:40.992
Have you got one? You must give.

00:37:41.017 --> 00:37:44.752
You see, they have really given a very elaborate... All are exhausted?

00:37:44.777 --> 00:37:46.132
No, doctor, I don't think they are (unclear)

00:37:46.157 --> 00:37:48.337
Sir, so we'll send it over to you.

00:37:48.337 --> 00:37:52.292
We have given in details all the things about this.

00:37:52.317 --> 00:37:55.632
How it is the mechanism within you, the subtle mechanism.

00:37:55.657 --> 00:37:58.777
How you get connected with the mains, you see.

00:37:58.802 --> 00:38:00.552
How you are made and everything.

00:38:00.577 --> 00:38:05.138
We have tried to do it in short and in quite a concise way,

00:38:05.163 --> 00:38:09.012
but we have given quite good information about it.

00:38:09.037 --> 00:38:15.300
And please have a look at it. What I think that I would like to meet the people of England

00:38:15.325 --> 00:38:21.092
who are actually sort of are... they think they are in charge, you see.

00:38:21.117 --> 00:38:22.737
I would like to talk to them about it.

00:38:22.737 --> 00:38:27.850
Because these young people, you see, they have no say.

00:38:27.875 --> 00:38:31.873
But this is the problem why I say you will end up going to politics

00:38:31.898 --> 00:38:34.362
because there's no way anybody in a Western type side

00:38:34.387 --> 00:38:38.098
can do anything without having some game,

00:38:38.123 --> 00:38:41.052
playing some game to do it and to bring it and be recognized.

00:38:41.077 --> 00:38:45.503
Because the people are, as you see, prisoners of their material way of life

00:38:45.528 --> 00:38:47.032
and it blots out the problems.

00:38:47.057 --> 00:38:50.572
At the moment they are living lives to blot out the problems, escape these lives.

00:38:50.597 --> 00:38:53.692
To take people away from escape these lives you have to offer them

00:38:53.717 --> 00:38:55.592
the most incredible inducement of all.

00:38:55.617 --> 00:38:59.470
It's not like a backward country where you can, like in Iran

00:38:59.495 --> 00:39:02.788
we've had, first you had the Shah, the monarchy, the glory,

00:39:02.813 --> 00:39:05.572
then suddenly you had Islam and the other way around.

00:39:05.597 --> 00:39:07.732
But this is the only thing that would take away.

00:39:07.757 --> 00:39:10.290
The Shah fell simply because he didn't understand

00:39:10.315 --> 00:39:14.992
that Islam was where you could get all these people (unclear)

00:39:15.017 --> 00:39:17.632
But I mean Englishmen are not concerned about that.

00:39:17.657 --> 00:39:21.830
Englishmen are concerned, I say, about their football and their television programs

00:39:21.855 --> 00:39:25.152
and their racing and everything else. Life is too full.

00:39:25.177 --> 00:39:27.912
So you have to slowly get things closed down.

00:39:27.937 --> 00:39:31.877
Like your government here is making prohibitions, so you have to start that way.

00:39:31.897 --> 00:39:36.572
Yes, you have to start. But I would say that your young people are going to (unclear).

00:39:36.597 --> 00:39:41.752
You see, to get into politics a prisoner as you said, it's a good idea.

00:39:41.777 --> 00:39:43.352
I have my attention on that.

00:39:43.377 --> 00:39:46.132
But I would still say I have to prepare them.

00:39:46.157 --> 00:39:52.272
They have to be something of a very higher personality to impress on others.

00:39:52.297 --> 00:39:56.512
If they are to be defiled like others are, I have to prepare them.

00:39:56.537 --> 00:39:59.652
Can you imagine, I worked only on six people for four years.

00:39:59.677 --> 00:40:04.918
Now I have so many, only on six people. They were all hippies and taking drugs,

00:40:04.943 --> 00:40:07.897
but now there are three hundred people who have given up drugs.

00:40:07.922 --> 00:40:13.072
They are beautiful people. And they have had all kinds of experiences and everything.

00:40:13.097 --> 00:40:14.792
So it is going to work out.

00:40:14.817 --> 00:40:18.732
But I mean, if you think that some people wouldn't be willing to do something,

00:40:18.757 --> 00:40:23.472
because you have to think that you could be the leaders tomorrow.

00:40:23.497 --> 00:40:30.112
But I mean, do you have, I never see when I am in I never see much on yoga and related subjects.

00:40:30.137 --> 00:40:34.953
You see, the trouble is we have been giving it in one yoga today,

00:40:34.978 --> 00:40:38.771
one article with very great difficulty they have published it.

00:40:38.796 --> 00:40:44.572
And in the TV people they gave all kinds of fake gurus, such an importance and empathy.

00:40:44.597 --> 00:40:48.808
They even had, what you call this, Muktan and the Amit, the Pope

00:40:48.833 --> 00:40:51.892
and this nonsense and these horrible people, you see.

00:40:51.917 --> 00:40:54.892
I don't know why they make such fuss out of these horrible people.

00:40:54.917 --> 00:40:58.990
Those who have ruined your young people, they have reached them completely,

00:40:59.015 --> 00:41:02.057
made money out of them. Why can't they see? And they give them.

00:41:02.057 --> 00:41:04.637
But for me, you see, somebody from India had gone

00:41:04.637 --> 00:41:08.732
who was to be filmed and so she said, why are you filming me?

00:41:08.757 --> 00:41:12.052
You have got Mataji who is the one who has given me all the power to do this.

00:41:12.077 --> 00:41:15.352
So they said, no, no, we have had many like that in Tamil Nadu.

00:41:15.377 --> 00:41:17.792
That's what it is.

00:41:17.817 --> 00:41:21.157
You see, it's very difficult now how to push forward things and

00:41:21.182 --> 00:41:25.135
we have a neighbour who is a MP, Conservative MP who is staying there

00:41:25.160 --> 00:41:32.732
and you cannot just talk to him about it. He is so mad with this politics.

00:41:32.757 --> 00:41:37.277
I told you, that's your answer, right? That's not yoga politics.

00:41:37.277 --> 00:41:38.812
But I have to neutralise.

00:41:38.837 --> 00:41:44.132
Now you just give some ideas to these boys how to neutralise their money.

00:41:44.157 --> 00:41:48.772
I think we'll work it out, we'll work it out. You will, I'm sure.

00:41:48.797 --> 00:41:53.812
We've done, by being, I mean, see, you know passive policy is no good to anybody.

00:41:53.837 --> 00:41:57.243
Because even when I mean even somebody like me who may be reaching a point

00:41:57.268 --> 00:42:01.867
where I may need something very soon.I mean, you're much too,

00:42:01.892 --> 00:42:05.272
how am I going to, anybody will get it my attention, it's impossible.

00:42:05.297 --> 00:42:10.992
Very soon if I go back to England, I will be immersed in the racing, football and everything else.

00:42:11.017 --> 00:42:14.272
It would be too much bother to come to England.

00:42:14.297 --> 00:42:17.183
You see, it is for them, it's not the problem.

00:42:17.208 --> 00:42:17.978
(Uclear)

00:42:18.003 --> 00:42:23.122
Tehran was this was the problem. You see, Tehran, they westernised it, you must be shocked.

00:42:23.147 --> 00:42:28.452
And they westernised so so much.

00:42:28.477 --> 00:42:32.732
(unclear) there's no alternative.

00:42:32.757 --> 00:42:38.497
But the point was that the leftists, not the leftists, the muslims...

00:42:38.497 --> 00:42:42.692
Just think of it. Absolutely.

00:42:42.717 --> 00:42:47.317
They really genuinely believe that they are people who are...

00:42:47.317 --> 00:42:52.613
These people in Paris have gone over the top on it. It's purely natural.